20:12.994 --> 20:14.909
- Nick!
- [groans]

20:14.952 --> 20:17.128
Happy.
- I found you.

20:17.172 --> 20:20.262
- [laughs]
Just like our first time.

20:20.306 --> 20:22.003
- What can I do, Nick?

20:22.046 --> 20:23.831
- Sure could use a drink.

20:23.874 --> 20:25.441
♪

20:25.485 --> 20:27.226
No, no, no.

20:27.269 --> 20:30.751
Not that.

20:30.794 --> 20:32.492
- Nick, I've been thinking.

20:32.535 --> 20:34.885
You can touch me.
No one else can.

20:34.929 --> 20:36.409
[Happy squeaks]

20:36.452 --> 20:37.888
[explosion]

20:37.932 --> 20:39.977
But why?
- Uh--

20:40.021 --> 20:44.243
- I think--I think it's because
you believe in me.

20:44.286 --> 20:46.201
- Fascinating.
- Uh-huh.

20:46.245 --> 20:50.118
Now, believe in this.

20:50.161 --> 20:52.294
- [gasps, laughs]

20:52.338 --> 20:54.340
Oh, sweet Jesus.

20:54.383 --> 20:56.037
- Bottom's up, buddy.

20:56.080 --> 20:58.387
[can pops]
[beer gurgling]

20:58.431 --> 21:00.781
♪

21:00.824 --> 21:03.262
- [grunts, sniffs]

21:03.305 --> 21:05.089
[growling]

21:05.133 --> 21:07.440
♪

21:07.483 --> 21:10.443
- Not so fast,
you cotton-tailed terrorist!

21:10.486 --> 21:12.314
[glass shattering]

21:12.358 --> 21:14.360
Over here, rodent!

21:14.403 --> 21:16.013
[chuckling]

21:18.538 --> 21:19.930
[glass shatters]

21:19.974 --> 21:21.454
[lights click]

21:21.497 --> 21:25.414
Your hippity-hoppity reign
of destruction ends tonight.

21:25.458 --> 21:27.198
[dramatic rock music]

21:27.242 --> 21:30.158
♪ Mega

21:30.201 --> 21:32.291
[children cheering]

21:32.334 --> 21:39.298
♪

21:44.085 --> 21:46.827
[cheering]

21:46.870 --> 21:51.135
♪

21:51.179 --> 21:53.921
- [chuckles]
Oh, no, no, no.

21:53.964 --> 21:55.444
You're not
going anywhere, daddy.

21:55.488 --> 21:58.055
I filled that syringe
with a dosage

21:58.099 --> 22:00.231
that would paralyze
a silverback gorilla,

22:00.275 --> 22:03.278
and then doubled it.

22:03.322 --> 22:06.629
- Should have tripled it.

22:06.673 --> 22:08.327
[yells, grunts]

22:08.370 --> 22:10.938
That was close.
[grunts]

22:10.981 --> 22:14.985
♪

22:15.029 --> 22:17.248
- [yells]

22:17.292 --> 22:18.946
- She's outside.
She's gonna meet us outside.

22:18.989 --> 22:20.600
all: Sonny! Sonny!

22:20.643 --> 22:22.645
- Whoo-hoo!
[laughs]

22:22.689 --> 22:25.169
all: Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

22:25.213 --> 22:27.868
Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

22:27.911 --> 22:34.918
♪

22:36.659 --> 22:39.009
- [choking]

22:39.053 --> 22:41.577
[grunts]

22:41.621 --> 22:44.580
[dramatic music]

22:44.624 --> 22:50.325
♪

22:50.369 --> 22:52.240
I--ugh.

22:52.283 --> 22:55.025
[both grunting]

22:55.069 --> 22:58.594
♪

22:58.638 --> 23:00.291
- [groans]

23:00.335 --> 23:02.642
all: Sonny! Sonny!
- No one gets out of here!

23:02.685 --> 23:05.427
[muffled screaming]

23:05.471 --> 23:07.690
- Come on, come on, come on!
Let's get out of here now!

23:07.734 --> 23:14.915
♪

23:24.098 --> 23:25.186
[bones crunching]

23:25.229 --> 23:26.970
- [grunts]

23:27.014 --> 23:32.541
♪

23:32.585 --> 23:35.718
[triumphant music]

23:35.762 --> 23:40.244
♪

23:40.288 --> 23:42.203
- [grunts]

23:42.246 --> 23:44.161
♪

23:44.205 --> 23:47.164
[straining]

23:47.208 --> 23:50.733
♪

23:50.777 --> 23:52.169
- [groaning]

23:52.213 --> 23:53.562
- Don't panic, everyone!

23:53.606 --> 23:57.131
I got this!

23:57.174 --> 23:59.568
- No, no!
Cut, cut, cut!

23:59.612 --> 24:02.571
[cheering]

24:02.615 --> 24:03.616
♪

24:03.659 --> 24:06.009
- Whoo!
[laughs]

24:06.053 --> 24:08.272
all: Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

24:08.316 --> 24:11.580
Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

24:11.624 --> 24:15.236
Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

24:15.279 --> 24:18.282
Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

24:18.326 --> 24:19.675
[ominous music]

24:19.719 --> 24:23.331
Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

24:23.374 --> 24:25.289
[children cheering]

24:25.333 --> 24:28.075
Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

24:28.118 --> 24:30.294
♪

24:30.338 --> 24:32.601
Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

24:32.645 --> 24:35.996
Sonny! Sonny! Sonny!

24:36.039 --> 24:38.346
- Hailey!

24:38.389 --> 24:43.743
♪

24:43.786 --> 24:47.137
- Hailey, don't do it--
[groans]

24:47.181 --> 24:48.748
Stop!

24:48.791 --> 24:51.228
Hailey...

24:51.272 --> 24:54.144
♪

24:54.188 --> 24:55.711
This is what Smoothie wants.

24:55.755 --> 24:58.192
[panting]

24:58.235 --> 25:01.369
This is what he's wanted
from the beginning.

25:01.412 --> 25:08.376
♪

25:08.419 --> 25:10.160
- I'm not doing this
for him, Dad.

25:10.204 --> 25:13.120
♪

25:13.163 --> 25:16.602
I'm doing it for me.

25:16.645 --> 25:19.648
[whooshing]

25:25.698 --> 25:26.742
- [grunts]

25:26.786 --> 25:28.048
[crowd screaming]

25:28.091 --> 25:29.571
- Nick!

25:29.615 --> 25:36.447
♪

25:36.491 --> 25:39.450
[dramatic music]

25:39.494 --> 25:46.501
♪

25:50.549 --> 25:52.551
[gunshot]

25:52.594 --> 25:53.595
[audience screaming]

25:53.639 --> 25:55.684
[gunshot]

25:55.728 --> 25:59.427
[screaming, chatter]

25:59.470 --> 26:02.343
- ♪ When Sonny gets blue

26:02.386 --> 26:04.563
♪ Hey eyes get

26:04.606 --> 26:08.218
[gunshot]

26:08.262 --> 26:11.134
♪ Then the rain begins

26:11.178 --> 26:14.573
♪ To fall

26:14.616 --> 26:16.487
[audience gasping]

26:16.531 --> 26:19.360
♪ Pitter, patter,
pitter, patter ♪

26:19.403 --> 26:20.666
- Sonny, Sonny!

26:20.709 --> 26:25.409
- ♪ Love is gone
so what can matter ♪

26:25.453 --> 26:26.410
♪ No sweet lovin' man

26:26.454 --> 26:27.586
- Sundrops.

26:27.629 --> 26:29.631
- ♪ Comes to call

26:29.675 --> 26:31.328
- All my little sundrops.

26:31.372 --> 26:33.896
Oh...
[laughs, coughs]

26:33.940 --> 26:36.377
[sniffs, groans]

26:36.420 --> 26:41.382
- ♪ She breathes a sigh
of sadness ♪

26:41.425 --> 26:44.254
♪ Like the wind that stirs

26:44.298 --> 26:46.517
- Boop.
[coughs]

26:46.561 --> 26:48.650
[sniffs]
You're not...

26:48.694 --> 26:51.740
You're not the fu--
you're not the future.

26:51.784 --> 26:53.394
No.

26:53.437 --> 26:54.656
You're not--
- Can I get a selfie?

26:54.700 --> 26:56.702
- You're not the future.

26:56.745 --> 26:58.747
♪

26:58.791 --> 27:01.750
I'm the--
I'm the--

27:01.794 --> 27:03.622
I'm the fu--

27:03.665 --> 27:05.624
I'm the future.

27:05.667 --> 27:06.668
I--

27:06.712 --> 27:08.801
- ♪ People used to love

27:08.844 --> 27:12.413
♪ Hear her laugh,
see her smile ♪

27:12.456 --> 27:14.284
[somber chatter]

27:14.328 --> 27:17.331
♪ That's how
she got her name ♪

27:17.374 --> 27:20.334
[dramatic music]

27:20.377 --> 27:23.250
♪

27:23.293 --> 27:27.689
- This is the NYPD!
This is an active crime scene!

27:27.733 --> 27:30.649
If you remain in this area,
you are in danger.

27:30.692 --> 27:33.347
Evacuate immediately.
- Huh.

27:33.390 --> 27:35.610
- Move calmly and swiftly
to the nearest exit.

27:35.654 --> 27:37.264
Repeat, you are--

27:37.307 --> 27:38.482
- Dad, Dad, Dad.
- Shh.

27:38.526 --> 27:39.875
- Dad, I'm--I'm sorry.

27:39.919 --> 27:41.790
- Shh, no, no, no.

27:41.834 --> 27:43.531
- ...calmly and swiftly
to the nearest exit.

27:43.574 --> 27:45.794
- It's not your fault.
I did this.

27:45.838 --> 27:47.970
- I'm sorry I said
I wanted things to go back

27:48.014 --> 27:49.798
to the way the used to be.

27:49.842 --> 27:51.844
I didn't mean it, I didn't.

27:51.887 --> 27:53.497
- I know.

27:53.541 --> 27:56.718
It's okay.

27:56.762 --> 27:59.503
You never needed
a fake dad anyway.

27:59.547 --> 28:01.810
- You're not a fake dad.

28:01.854 --> 28:03.594
♪

28:03.638 --> 28:05.814
You're real...

28:05.858 --> 28:09.209
and I don't want you to go.

28:09.252 --> 28:11.733
[somber music]

28:11.777 --> 28:14.736
- [labored breathing]

28:14.780 --> 28:16.303
♪

28:16.346 --> 28:20.002
- Move calmly and swiftly
to the nearest exit.

28:20.046 --> 28:24.485
♪

28:24.528 --> 28:27.706
- Drop the weapon!
Drop the weapon!

28:27.749 --> 28:30.491
- Any other active shooter?
- Ma'am, drop the weapon.

28:30.534 --> 28:32.754
Hands where I can see them.
- Cover the corners!

28:35.757 --> 28:37.585
- Sonny's show
was the highest-rated

28:37.628 --> 28:39.021
Easter Sunday broadcast ever.

28:39.065 --> 28:40.196
By the time he ate the bullet,

28:40.240 --> 28:42.068
he was doing
Super Bowl numbers.

28:42.111 --> 28:43.983
- He was right,
the show was a hit.

28:44.026 --> 28:45.419
- It's ironic.

28:45.462 --> 28:47.334
Poor guy never lived
to see the overnights.

28:47.377 --> 28:49.989
- I always knew it would work.
- What about Brooks?

28:54.254 --> 28:55.385
- Replaceable.

28:55.429 --> 28:57.779
- No, I mean,
shouldn't we say something?

28:57.823 --> 29:00.173
Tell someone?
I mean, his family?

29:00.216 --> 29:02.088
- Why ruin a great
feel-good story?

29:02.131 --> 29:03.872
- We should get something going
with the guy.

29:03.916 --> 29:05.178
The one who killed Santa Claus.

29:05.221 --> 29:06.527
- Now we're talking.

29:06.570 --> 29:08.181
He's like a real-life
John McClane.

29:08.224 --> 29:09.835
- Exclusive with
Fareed Zakaria.

29:09.878 --> 29:12.794
- Screw that.
Why not his own show?

29:12.838 --> 29:14.361
- Wait, wait, let's don't
get ahead of ourselves.

29:14.404 --> 29:16.232
Didn't he die?

29:16.276 --> 29:18.800
- Get him over.
Clear.

29:18.844 --> 29:20.759
[electricity zapping]

29:20.802 --> 29:22.456
[dramatic music]

29:23.413 --> 29:24.458
- Somebody check that.

29:24.501 --> 29:26.503
[monitor flat-lining]

29:28.854 --> 29:30.769
- Nick.
Wake up, Nick.

29:30.812 --> 29:33.859
- Call it.
- Time of death, 9:53 p.m.

29:33.902 --> 29:35.817
- All right, that's a wrap.

29:35.861 --> 29:37.819
You wanna grab margaritas
at Chili's?

29:37.863 --> 29:39.952
- [sighs] Nah, "The Voice"
is on tonight.

29:39.995 --> 29:43.129
- No, you can't just--
this is somebody's father!

29:43.172 --> 29:44.826
Somebody's son!

29:44.870 --> 29:46.828
Somebody's best friend!

29:46.872 --> 29:48.177
Wake him up, Doc!

29:48.221 --> 29:50.223
Use the zappers, come on!

29:50.266 --> 29:52.268
- Wait.

29:53.574 --> 29:55.881
Do you feel that?

29:55.924 --> 29:57.447
That breeze?
- No, uh-uh.

29:57.491 --> 29:59.972
No, no, no, don't start
that shit, Doc.

30:00.015 --> 30:01.887
That "you can feel
the spirit leaving them

30:01.930 --> 30:04.237
as they slough off
the motherfucking mortal coil."

30:04.280 --> 30:05.455
I'm not having that shit.

30:05.499 --> 30:07.414
I will walk
the fuck right out of here

30:07.457 --> 30:09.808
and you will not see
my black ass ever again.

30:09.851 --> 30:11.418
Try me.

30:11.461 --> 30:14.029
- Oh, there are millions
of "IFs" out there

30:14.073 --> 30:15.422
just like you, Happy.

30:15.465 --> 30:17.554
- Waiting for the moment
our young friends

30:17.598 --> 30:20.035
stop believing completely...

30:20.079 --> 30:22.908
- And we blink out
of existence.

30:22.951 --> 30:25.345
- When your friend
stops believing, you disappear.

30:25.388 --> 30:26.912
- I die...

30:26.955 --> 30:29.915
if she dies.

30:29.958 --> 30:33.092
Well, I guess
this is it, then.

30:33.135 --> 30:35.355
I've lived, I've loved.

30:35.398 --> 30:38.140
I've done things no other
imaginary friend has ever done.

30:38.184 --> 30:40.490
Now it's time for me to go.

30:40.534 --> 30:42.449
The great pineapple pasture
in the sky

30:42.492 --> 30:46.279
where IFs frolic forever
under clown-colored clouds.

30:46.322 --> 30:48.411
Goodbye, sweet world.

30:48.455 --> 30:51.937
Goodbye, Hailey,
wherever you are.

30:51.980 --> 30:54.330
Goodbye, partner.

31:02.512 --> 31:04.863
I'm...

31:04.906 --> 31:06.995
not dead.

31:09.171 --> 31:11.260
Why the heck ain't I dead?

31:14.263 --> 31:17.136
[angelic classical music]

31:17.179 --> 31:24.186
♪

31:33.369 --> 31:35.502
- Welcome, Nick.

31:35.545 --> 31:38.940
Size doesn't matter here.

31:38.984 --> 31:40.942
♪

31:40.986 --> 31:42.944
My breasts are filled

31:42.988 --> 31:46.513
with the finest bourbons.

31:46.556 --> 31:50.691
Suckle them for eternity.

31:50.734 --> 31:56.610
♪

32:07.229 --> 32:09.275
- Hello, Nick.

32:11.668 --> 32:13.279
- Motherfucker.

32:13.322 --> 32:15.107
If you're gonna cock-block me
for all eternity,

32:15.150 --> 32:16.325
we're gonna have a problem.

32:16.369 --> 32:18.501
- No, no, Nick, I just
come here sometimes.

32:18.545 --> 32:21.069
You know, pop into the party.

32:21.113 --> 32:25.291
Which is absolutely
fucking bestial.

32:25.334 --> 32:27.597
[laughs]
No, but I wanted

32:27.641 --> 32:30.383
to tell you, Nick,
it doesn't have to be this way.

32:30.426 --> 32:32.385
You can turn back.

32:32.428 --> 32:35.040
- I don't think
you got the memo, asshole.

32:35.083 --> 32:36.519
I flat-lined.
Bellied up.

32:36.563 --> 32:38.478
Bagged and tagged.

32:38.521 --> 32:40.349
Man, is it hot in here.

32:40.393 --> 32:41.568
- I can still bring you back.

32:41.611 --> 32:43.265
- What the fuck
would I want that for?

32:43.309 --> 32:46.138
I been dreaming of this moment
my entire life.

32:46.181 --> 32:47.966
[tense music]

32:48.009 --> 32:50.229
- What about your little girl?

32:50.272 --> 32:51.708
♪

32:51.752 --> 32:53.406
- Let's face facts.

32:53.449 --> 32:56.148
I think there's one thing
we've all learned here.

32:56.191 --> 32:57.976
♪

32:58.019 --> 33:00.674
That she's better off
without me.

33:00.717 --> 33:04.634
- Hmm, difficult point
to argue.

33:04.678 --> 33:08.247
Oh, then there is
the small matter of revenge.

33:08.290 --> 33:11.728
♪

33:11.772 --> 33:13.992
- "Revenge"?

33:14.035 --> 33:15.428
I don't have a vengeful bone
in my body.

33:15.471 --> 33:18.431
- Oh, Nick, don't be tedious.
Of course you do.

33:18.474 --> 33:21.608
Everybody loves revenge.

33:21.651 --> 33:25.090
I mean, can you really
shuffle off to the great beyond

33:25.133 --> 33:27.657
knowing that the man
who bested you

33:27.701 --> 33:29.050
is still out there somewhere?

33:29.094 --> 33:30.486
Can you?

33:30.530 --> 33:32.793
You know who
I'm talking about.

33:32.836 --> 33:34.490
- Tick, tock, time to rock.

33:34.534 --> 33:37.406
I'm going to show you
why they call me--

33:37.450 --> 33:38.538
- Smoothie.

33:38.581 --> 33:40.453
- Yes.

33:40.496 --> 33:43.717
♪

33:43.760 --> 33:46.589
- But there's
the finest bourbon.

33:46.633 --> 33:51.116
♪

33:51.159 --> 33:52.421
- [chuckles]

33:52.465 --> 33:54.728
- Why is it so hot in here?

33:54.771 --> 33:56.121
[gas hissing]

33:56.164 --> 33:59.472
- Death drums his fingers
and waits for us all,

33:59.515 --> 34:01.648
even me.

34:01.691 --> 34:03.606
I think he can wait
a little longer.

34:03.650 --> 34:05.304
Don't you?

34:05.347 --> 34:10.265
♪

34:10.309 --> 34:12.093
- Well, maybe just
a little bit longer.

34:12.137 --> 34:14.313
- Splendid!
[laughing]

34:14.356 --> 34:16.402
Ooh, one small thing.
- Yeah?

34:16.445 --> 34:18.708
- If I bring you back,
you belong to me for all time.

34:18.752 --> 34:20.275
Okay?
- What?

34:20.319 --> 34:23.278
[gas hissing]

34:23.322 --> 34:29.719
♪

34:29.763 --> 34:32.722
[dramatic music]

34:32.766 --> 34:39.773
♪

34:43.472 --> 34:46.432
[flames roaring]

34:46.475 --> 34:49.435
[tense music]

34:49.478 --> 34:52.699
♪

34:54.309 --> 34:56.311
I've woken up worse.

35:00.228 --> 35:02.012
- Okay, Hansen.

35:02.056 --> 35:04.102
Your ride's here.

35:04.145 --> 35:05.668
- Is it grandma?

35:05.712 --> 35:08.062
- No, honey, it's your aunt.

35:08.106 --> 35:10.064
- I have an aunt?

35:10.108 --> 35:13.067
[curious music]

35:13.111 --> 35:16.157
- Nice jacket.

35:16.201 --> 35:18.681
- It's supposed to make me
look more normal.

35:18.725 --> 35:20.727
I'm sure you can relate.

35:20.770 --> 35:22.685
- It's not working.

35:22.729 --> 35:25.035
♪

35:25.079 --> 35:27.777
I don't understand.

35:27.821 --> 35:31.694
- Well, your mom and dad
listed me as your next of kin.

35:31.738 --> 35:35.133
So, looks like I got
a roommate for a while.

35:35.176 --> 35:37.047
♪

35:37.091 --> 35:39.180
- Why would she put me
with you?

35:39.224 --> 35:40.834
- Maybe she thought
you could use

35:40.877 --> 35:43.141
a good female role model.

35:51.236 --> 35:53.890
- What happened to your hand?

35:53.934 --> 35:57.024
- Story for another day.

35:57.067 --> 35:59.983
Feet off the dash.

36:00.027 --> 36:01.811
[Mr. Mister's "Book of Love"]

36:01.855 --> 36:03.726
- [barks, growls]

36:03.770 --> 36:06.207
♪

36:06.251 --> 36:08.078
- Where is everyone?

36:08.122 --> 36:10.994
- You live under a mushroom
or something?

36:11.038 --> 36:13.954
Not you.

36:13.997 --> 36:16.870
- I don't understand.
- Oh, sorry.

36:16.913 --> 36:21.091
I guess you missed
the IF mass genocide on Sunday.

36:21.135 --> 36:23.355
That Bob's Big Boy-looking perv
all the kids love

36:23.398 --> 36:25.095
got murdered
on national television.

36:25.139 --> 36:27.228
No big deal.
I'm sure you can DVR it.

36:27.272 --> 36:29.926
- Oh, that.

36:29.970 --> 36:31.624
I was there.

36:31.667 --> 36:33.016
- Dude.

36:33.060 --> 36:34.104
I'm sorry.

36:34.148 --> 36:35.932
- Oh, forget it.

36:35.976 --> 36:37.934
- The usual?
On the house, man.

36:37.978 --> 36:39.893
- No, thanks.

36:39.936 --> 36:42.025
Hey, you haven't seen
Peep around, have you?

36:42.069 --> 36:44.376
- Peep?
Yeah, she's here.

36:44.419 --> 36:46.378
I let her use the back room.

36:46.421 --> 36:50.425
Hey, wait, you probably don't
want to go back there.

36:50.469 --> 36:52.122
Suit yourself, buddy.

36:52.166 --> 36:55.125
[both moaning]

36:55.169 --> 36:56.779
- Oh, yes, sir!

36:56.823 --> 36:58.128
Yes, sir!

36:58.172 --> 36:59.782
Three bags full!

36:59.826 --> 37:01.741
- Bo?
[both gasp]

37:01.784 --> 37:04.831
- Ah, crap.
- Oh, uh, hey, Happy.

37:06.136 --> 37:09.139
What's good, man?

37:09.183 --> 37:10.271
[chattering]

37:10.315 --> 37:11.838
- ♪ The voices sing

37:11.881 --> 37:14.275
- ♪ The book of love
will open up ♪

37:14.319 --> 37:16.146
- I was, uh...

37:16.190 --> 37:17.800
distraught?

37:17.844 --> 37:20.977
- ♪ Take these broken wings

37:21.021 --> 37:23.197
♪ You've got to learn to fly

37:23.241 --> 37:26.026
♪ Learn to live,
love so free ♪

37:26.069 --> 37:28.333
♪ And when we hear

37:28.376 --> 37:31.727
- You'll be all right there
for a while.

37:31.771 --> 37:34.948
Merry lost her father, too,
you know.

37:35.992 --> 37:37.211
I just want you to know

37:37.255 --> 37:39.996
that none of this
is your fault.

37:40.040 --> 37:42.695
- We all just did
what we had to do.

37:42.738 --> 37:44.262
That's all.

37:44.305 --> 37:47.265
[dark music]

37:47.308 --> 37:50.006
♪

37:50.050 --> 37:52.270
- I'm coming for you.

37:52.313 --> 37:54.010
You stay strong, Hailey.

37:54.054 --> 37:55.925
I promise,
no matter what it takes,

37:55.969 --> 38:00.016
I will come for you.

38:00.060 --> 38:03.019
- No, Mom.

38:03.063 --> 38:05.761
I'll come for you.

38:05.805 --> 38:08.764
[dark electronic music]

38:08.808 --> 38:12.768
♪

38:12.812 --> 38:15.771
[cars honking]

38:15.815 --> 38:22.822
♪

38:39.404 --> 38:40.405
[dog barking]

38:40.448 --> 38:41.841
- Hey, hey, hey!

38:41.884 --> 38:44.060
Da-da-da-da, yeah, you.

38:44.104 --> 38:51.111
♪

38:53.809 --> 38:55.245
- Don't look at that!

38:55.289 --> 38:57.291
Look at this!

38:57.335 --> 39:04.342
♪

39:10.435 --> 39:13.394
[cars honking]

39:13.438 --> 39:15.831
♪

39:15.875 --> 39:19.444
[grumbles]

39:19.487 --> 39:21.881
[groaning]

39:21.924 --> 39:23.839
[whooshing]

39:23.883 --> 39:27.800
[triumphant music]

39:29.367 --> 39:31.238
[labored breathing]

39:31.281 --> 39:34.154
I always thought I knew
what my purpose was,

39:34.197 --> 39:36.591
but that's all gone now.

39:36.635 --> 39:38.332
I don't even know
what I am anymore.

39:38.376 --> 39:40.856
What the heck am I?

39:40.900 --> 39:42.292
- That's a very good question.

39:42.336 --> 39:44.425
That's a very good question.

39:44.469 --> 39:47.123
You seem to be, like,
a kind of a mash-up

39:47.167 --> 39:50.431
of random images
from a child's brain

39:50.475 --> 39:54.566
that's, uh, obtained
some kind of autonomy.

39:54.609 --> 39:56.350
Isn't that wild?

39:56.394 --> 39:57.960
- God?

39:58.004 --> 40:01.442
- Let's call me, uh,
an imaginary friend.

40:01.486 --> 40:05.925
Only, my friend, uh,
happens to be, you know,

40:05.968 --> 40:07.448
a whole civilization.

40:07.492 --> 40:09.189
At this point, thankfully,

40:09.232 --> 40:13.019
an ever-dwindling portion
of civilization.

40:13.062 --> 40:14.629
That's a funny name for it,
isn't it?

40:14.673 --> 40:16.283
"Civilization."

40:16.326 --> 40:18.328
Geez, insects
are more civilized.

40:18.372 --> 40:20.635
- You, an--
an imaginary friend?

40:20.679 --> 40:23.856
That's silly,
everyone believes in you.

40:23.899 --> 40:25.466
- They do?

40:25.510 --> 40:27.512
Really?
[scoffs]

40:27.555 --> 40:28.600
To tell you the truth,

40:28.643 --> 40:30.253
I got days
when I feel just like you.

40:30.297 --> 40:32.473
Like, "What the hell
am I even doing up here?"

40:32.517 --> 40:34.040
I mean, yes, you're right.

40:34.083 --> 40:36.869
People--people talk about me,

40:36.912 --> 40:39.915
but they don't really believe.

40:39.959 --> 40:42.396
I mean, they pretend to.

40:42.440 --> 40:44.442
But look at them.

40:44.485 --> 40:46.095
Geez.

40:46.139 --> 40:47.967
But, you know,
that's exactly my point.

40:48.010 --> 40:50.883
Every day, I hear these
sanctimonious assholes saying,

40:50.926 --> 40:53.494
"God told me this,"
and "God spoke to me that."

40:53.538 --> 40:56.018
Um, n-no.

40:56.062 --> 40:58.107
No, I did--did not.

40:58.151 --> 41:00.675
I dunno what voice
you're hearing,

41:00.719 --> 41:03.199
but, uh, it's not mine.

41:03.243 --> 41:04.374
Not mine.

41:04.418 --> 41:05.941
- But what about prayers?

41:05.985 --> 41:08.509
- Prayers?
That's--that's for them.

41:08.553 --> 41:11.512
That's not for me, not for us.

41:11.556 --> 41:13.514
Uh, hey, if I played favorites

41:13.558 --> 41:17.039
based on who, uh,
stroked my ego more,

41:17.083 --> 41:18.214
you know, what kind of--

41:18.258 --> 41:19.564
what kind of jagoff
would I be?

41:19.607 --> 41:21.609
No, prayers, mm,

41:21.653 --> 41:24.046
are like those buttons
at the crosswalk.

41:24.090 --> 41:26.571
You press them
to make you feel better,

41:26.614 --> 41:28.398
but you're not gonna
change the traffic

41:28.442 --> 41:29.922
by hitting a button.

41:29.965 --> 41:31.576
If I were you,
here's what I'd do:

41:31.619 --> 41:33.578
I'd focus on doing
what I do best.

41:33.621 --> 41:35.057
Being a friend.

41:35.101 --> 41:37.059
Forget the "imaginary" part.

41:37.103 --> 41:38.539
The--the nice lady
is rotting away

41:38.583 --> 41:40.585
in the stoney lonesome
for manslaughter.

41:40.628 --> 41:42.325
The little girl
is about to turn into

41:42.369 --> 41:44.545
some kind of witch assassin

41:44.589 --> 41:48.157
on the trail
of an evil, secret society.

41:48.201 --> 41:50.420
It's very dangerous, man.

41:50.464 --> 41:53.423
And, you know, Sax, the idiot?

41:53.467 --> 41:55.208
You know, he's a half-zombie

41:55.251 --> 41:59.255
in the service of some kind
of schizophrenic demi-god.

41:59.299 --> 42:02.128
- But Nick's dead.

42:02.171 --> 42:04.652
- Um, yeah, well,
you might wanna--

42:04.696 --> 42:06.567
you might wanna check on that.

42:06.611 --> 42:08.656
Good talk, good talk.

42:08.700 --> 42:10.092
I gotta ghost, man.

42:10.136 --> 42:12.094
You know,
this ain't my only gig.

42:12.138 --> 42:15.010
Huh, maybe my time here is--

42:15.054 --> 42:16.446
is coming to an end.

42:16.490 --> 42:18.361
Huh.

42:18.405 --> 42:20.538
[thunder rumbles]

42:20.581 --> 42:23.018
Anyway, ball up.

42:23.062 --> 42:25.717
Ball up, little--
little horsey.

42:25.760 --> 42:27.370
Drop those tiny blue testicles,

42:27.414 --> 42:31.418
'cause this shit's about
to get, uh, dark.

42:31.461 --> 42:34.595
[ominous music]

42:36.641 --> 42:39.600
[gentle music]

42:39.644 --> 42:46.041
♪

42:47.477 --> 42:49.349
- Hey, uh, this came
for you today.

42:49.392 --> 42:52.134
It's from Europe.

42:52.178 --> 42:54.572
- Thank you.
I've been waiting for this.

42:54.615 --> 42:57.575
[tense music]

42:57.618 --> 43:01.579
♪

43:36.788 --> 43:39.747
[New Order's "Blue Monday"
playing over speakers]

43:39.791 --> 43:44.665
♪

43:44.709 --> 43:46.667
[sighs]

43:46.711 --> 43:52.368
♪

43:52.412 --> 43:54.196
- [grunts]

43:54.240 --> 44:01.247
♪

44:07.862 --> 44:10.343
- [sighs]

44:10.386 --> 44:12.084
How?

44:12.127 --> 44:15.609
♪

44:15.653 --> 44:17.698
- [grunts]

44:17.742 --> 44:23.661
♪

44:23.704 --> 44:26.185
[both grunt]

44:26.228 --> 44:29.449
- I am so happy right now.

44:29.492 --> 44:30.842
- Me, too.
- I thought you were--

44:30.885 --> 44:32.582
- Dead.
I know, right?

44:32.626 --> 44:33.845
- Bullet to the chest
from your daughter,

44:33.888 --> 44:35.498
autopsy, incinerator.

44:35.542 --> 44:36.848
- Mere trifles.

44:36.891 --> 44:38.545
- And then you wouldn't
have been able to--

44:38.588 --> 44:41.156
- Kill you myself.
- Exactly.

44:41.200 --> 44:42.636
♪

44:42.680 --> 44:45.117
You know, for people like us,

44:45.160 --> 44:49.164
it's never easy
to find a worthy adversary.

44:49.208 --> 44:51.732
A truly meaningful death.

44:51.776 --> 44:54.517
- I know exactly what you mean.

44:54.561 --> 44:57.738
♪

44:57.782 --> 44:59.435
Enough with the chitchat.

44:59.479 --> 45:01.786
- Ah, I want you to know...

45:01.829 --> 45:04.136
that I have enjoyed our tango.

45:04.179 --> 45:06.878
- [sighs]

45:06.921 --> 45:09.750
Goodbye, Smoothie.
- See ya.

45:09.794 --> 45:13.754
- ♪ Tell me how do I feel

45:13.798 --> 45:17.845
♪ Tell me now
how do I feel ♪

45:19.673 --> 45:21.283
- So...
[sniffs]

45:21.327 --> 45:23.721
What do you want to be
for Halloween this year?

45:23.764 --> 45:25.723
Hmm.

45:25.766 --> 45:28.726
[sinister music]

45:28.769 --> 45:35.733
♪

45:37.822 --> 45:39.301
- I know!

45:39.345 --> 45:41.782
How about psycho Santa Claus?

45:41.826 --> 45:43.305
♪

45:43.349 --> 45:44.567
No?

45:44.611 --> 45:46.787
All right, honey, you okay?

45:46.831 --> 45:53.794
♪
